{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem\/init(_:isOn:extraLabel:description:icon:flipIcon:isOutlined:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:action:)-6ivfn","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem\/init(_:isOn:extraLabel:description:icon:flipIcon:isOutlined:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:action:)-9pia5","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem\/init(_:tableName:bundle:isOn:extraLabel:description:icon:flipIcon:isOutlined:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:action:)-1z883","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem\/init(_:tableName:bundle:isOn:extraLabel:description:icon:flipIcon:isOutlined:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:action:)-8hs6n"]},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem\/body"]},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem\/View-Implementations"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSRadioItem","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Layouts","level":2,"text":"Layouts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"reversed","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": like the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" layout but with a trailing radio indicator and a leading optional decorative icon"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Indicator-states","level":2,"text":"Indicator states"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The radio indicator has two available states:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"selected","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the radio is filled with a filled circle, the user has made the action to select the radio"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"unselected","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": the radio is empty, does not contain anything, the user has made the action to unselect or did not select yet the radio"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Particular-cases","level":2,"text":"Particular cases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem","type":"reference"},{"text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isError"},{"text":" flag is risen.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem"},{"text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet but this component must not be considered","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"as disabled.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The radio can be also outlined in some cases.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component does not follow the right-to-left (RTL) \/ left-to-right (LTR) mode returned by the system as it could have some meaning"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to have for example the indicator in trailing position for LTR mode and vice versa."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However, if the component has an icon in leading position (RTL mode) or in trailing position (LTR), the content of the icon is never changed."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It could lead to a loss of meaning or semantics in the icon. Thus a specific flag can be used to flip the icon content whatever the layout direction is."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It prevents the user do implement its own rules to flip or not image."}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Rich text","anchor":"Rich-text"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rich text can only be used for error messages.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Strong text can be used sparingly to highlight key information within the content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"No other text styles should be used."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Underlined text must not be applied manually (e.g. in error message), as it is commonly associated with hyperlinks and may mislead users."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Always check the results of rich text mode with high contrast, light and dark modes, and Voice Over vocalization.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and optional texts and a custom radio trait."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"No accessibility identifier is defined in OUDS side as this value remains in the users hands."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","level":2,"text":"Forbidden by design"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component."}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component."}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSRadioItem","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"can be used outside a dedicated picker, thus it does not need any tag and associated type."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an unselected state","    @Published var selection: Bool = false","","    \/\/ A leading radio with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $selection)","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSRadioItem(LocalizedStringKey(\"option_label\"), bundle: Bundle.module, isOn: $selection)","","    \/\/ A leading radio with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $selection, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading radio with a label, and an additional label but without text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $selection, extraLabel: \"The Beatles\")","","    \/\/ A leading radio with an additional label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $selection, extraLabel: \"The Beatles\", description: \"1967\")","","    \/\/ A trailing radio with a label, a description, an icon, a divider and is about an error.","    \/\/ The reversed layout will be used here.","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                  isOn: $selection,","                  description: \"Put your hand in mine\",","                  icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"),","                  isReversed: true,","                  isError: true,","                  hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                  isOn: $selection,","                  isError: true,","                  errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                  hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading radio with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Rescue from this world!\", isOn: $selection)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related radio as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $selection, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $selection, isReadOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}]},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSRadioItem(\"Cocorico !\",","                  isOn: $selection,","                  icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                  flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft,","                  isInversed: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-radio-button"}]},{"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_radioItem_Orange"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_radioItem_OrangeCompact"}]},{"text":"Sosh","anchor":"Sosh","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_radioItem_Sosh","type":"image"}]},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_radioItem_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Version","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.4.0 (Figma component design version)"}]}]},{"style":"note","name":"Since","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.12.0"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsradioitem"]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"15.0","name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"16.0","name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"11.0","name":"watchOS","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSRadioItem","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents13OUDSRadioItemV","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSRadioItem","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"OUDSRadioItem"},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Radio button item is a UI element that allows to select a single option from a set of mutually exclusive choices."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Radio button item covers a wider range of contexts by a